    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="754"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24172/10.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Wilson refers to the embassy’s telegram of the 21st instant, and states that
                    the governor of California has been advised of its contents. <pb facs="0839"
                        n="727" xml:id="pg_727"/> Instructs him to insist that Garcia be rearrested
                    and detained for treaty period on new charge of assault with intent to commit
                    murder. Calls attention to department’s April 10, 1909,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d754fn1">See <ref target="frus1909#pg_417">Foreign Relations, 1909,
                            p. 417</ref>.</note> and directs him to advise the governor of
                    California when new period of detention will expire.</p>
            </div>
